*   **Data-Hypothesis Mismatch (Fatal Flaw):** The hypothesis assumes that oxide precursors and their corresponding carbonates share the same `space_group`. This is physically incorrect. Carbonation involves a fundamental change in stoichiometry and coordination environment (e.g., CaO [Fm-3m] to CaCO₃ [R-3c]). Grouping by symmetry will result in an empty set for almost all valid reaction pairs.
